smoke (off)
Homonym Number:
Word Class:verb
Sense Number:
Definition:to depart, get going; to depart hastily and unobtrusively; to shoot through
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain:[none]
Region:[none]
See:-
Pronunciation:
Notes: Jim Cameron writes: NSOD gives this as <i>Austral.</i>. Not in Cassells. No NZ dictionary  entry but I have heard it occasionally since the 50s.
